
1.convert a string to a list of its characters

my_string = "hello"
my_list = list(my_string)
print(my_list) 
 [ OUTPUT OF THE PROGRAM.
    ['h', 'e', 'l', 'l', 'o'].
    
 2. characters back to a string.
 
     my_list = ['h', 'e', 'l', 'l', 'o']
my_string = ''.join(my_list)
print(my_string) 
[ OUTPUT OF THE PROGRAM.
   hello     ]
   
   
3.convert a single character to a string (or vice versa).
 
 my_char = 'a'
my_string = str(my_char)
print(my_string) 

my_string = "hello"
my_char = my_string[0]
print(my_char) 

[ OUTPUT OF THE PROGRAM.
   a
   h     ]

